Third generation cousins (or 'third cousins' for short) are people who share [[great great grandparents]].Third cousins share 12.5% of the same ancestry. Example:

Brother A has a full blooded brother named Brother B.

Brother A has a son name A1 and brother B has a son named B1. A1 and B1 are 1st generation cousins. 

A1 has a son named A2 and B1 has a son named B2. A2 and B2 are second generation cousins.

A2 has a son named A3 and B2 has a son named B3. A3 and B3 are third cousins. A3 and B3 share great grandparents, that is, the parents of Brother A and Brother B. They do not share ALL of their great great grandparents, only two out of 16.